```class Solution {
public:
    int trailingZeroes(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            n /= 5;
            count += n;
        }
        return count;
    }
};```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution counts the number of factors of 5 in n!, as each trailing zero is created by a factor of 2 and a factor of 5, and there are usually more factors of 2 than 5. The while loop iterates until n becomes 0, effectively counting the factors of 5 in n!.

